390
00:30:32,831 --> 00:30:34,874
The briefing begins immediately.

391
00:30:35,417 --> 00:30:37,043
Join the other recruits.

392
00:30:37,127 --> 00:30:38,920
Wait a minute!
Wait a minute!

393
00:30:39,171 --> 00:30:41,047
Wait a minute!
What are you talking
about, recruits?

394
00:30:41,131 --> 00:30:42,840
(ALL MUTTERING)

395
00:30:44,384 --> 00:30:46,135
I don't believe this.

396
00:30:47,638 --> 00:30:49,180
(ALL MUTTERING)

397
00:30:49,264 --> 00:30:53,518
MAN ON PA:
Attention. Attention, please.
Ambassador Enduran has arrived

398
00:30:53,602 --> 00:30:56,896
and will now address
Starfighter Command personnel.

399
00:30:59,816 --> 00:31:03,694
As you all know, we have
been on a desperate quest. . .

400
00:31:03,779 --> 00:31:05,530
Excuse me. Excuse me.

401
00:31:05,614 --> 00:31:06,739
ENDURAN: . . .to find
Starfighters and navigators.

402
00:31:06,823 --> 00:31:08,449
(SCREAMS IN PAIN)

403
00:31:08,617 --> 00:31:09,951
(GRUNTING)

404
00:31:10,744 --> 00:31:14,288
I should. . . I should
crush you to gorun dust!

405
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:17,833
I'm sorry. . .
It was an accident.

406
00:31:17,918 --> 00:31:19,460
I didn't mean to
step on your. . .

407
00:31:20,254 --> 00:31:21,587
Whatever that is.

408
00:31:21,672 --> 00:31:22,755
ALIEN: (WHISPERING)
Hideous creature.

409
00:31:22,839 --> 00:31:24,340
ENDURAN: If I may continue.

410
00:31:25,300 --> 00:31:26,801
Our forces have. . .

411
00:31:26,885 --> 00:31:28,386
You don't trifle with a Bogati.

412
00:31:28,470 --> 00:31:29,887
They love to fight.

413
00:31:29,972 --> 00:31:32,139
That's why they're
perfect for this war.

414
00:31:34,142 --> 00:31:35,142
Did you say "war"?

415
00:31:35,227 --> 00:31:36,227
But of course!

416
00:31:36,311 --> 00:31:38,563
Why else do you
think you're here?

417
00:31:38,647 --> 00:31:40,648
You were recruited
by the Star League
to defend. . .

418
00:31:40,732 --> 00:31:44,485
". . .to defend
the Frontier against Xur
and the Ko-Dan Armada."

419
00:31:46,863 --> 00:31:52,326
Eons ago,
our ancestors created
our great Frontier,

420
00:31:52,411 --> 00:31:54,662
a barrier of energy

421
00:31:54,746 --> 00:31:57,915
encircling the peaceful
systems of the universe,

422
00:31:58,625 --> 00:32:02,837
and forever shutting out
the scourge that lurks beyond.

423
00:32:05,048 --> 00:32:09,594
Fellow Rylans,
because of a dark betrayal,

424
00:32:09,678 --> 00:32:11,637
our Frontier
will soon collapse.

425
00:32:11,722 --> 00:32:13,139
(ALL MURMURING)

426
00:32:14,349 --> 00:32:19,478
So we turn to you,
Starfighters and
your navigators.

427
00:32:19,563 --> 00:32:23,190
For of all the billions
of creatures in the Star League,

428
00:32:23,275 --> 00:32:26,777
only you few were
found to possess the

429
00:32:28,905 --> 00:32:30,031
gift.

430
00:32:31,575 --> 00:32:34,660
You, and you alone,

431
00:32:34,745 --> 00:32:38,497
stand between us
and the black terror
of the Ko-Dan.

432
00:32:40,792 --> 00:32:44,295
Victory or death!

433
00:32:44,379 --> 00:32:47,423
ALL: Victory or death!
Victory or death!

434
00:32:47,507 --> 00:33:05,066
Victory or death!
Victory or death!

435
00:33:05,567 --> 00:33:08,611
MAN ON PA: Now,
Starfighters, if you will
reach underneath your seats,

436
00:33:08,695 --> 00:33:12,156
you will find a packet
which contains one hand...

437
00:33:16,036 --> 00:33:18,996
This is a restricted area,
off-limits to. . .

438
00:33:20,749 --> 00:33:21,749
(LAUGHING)

439
00:33:21,833 --> 00:33:24,794
My apologies, Starfighter.

440
00:33:24,878 --> 00:33:28,214
Star Navigator First Class Grig
at your service, sir!

441
00:33:28,298 --> 00:33:29,757
(LAUGHING)

442
00:33:30,842 --> 00:33:34,220
Hi. I'm Alex Rogan.
I was playing this
game back home,

443
00:33:34,304 --> 00:33:35,429
and this guy came up to me.

444
00:33:35,514 --> 00:33:37,348
Only he's not a guy.
He's an alien, right?

445
00:33:37,432 --> 00:33:40,184
And I get into his car.
Only it's not a car.
It's a spaceship.

446
00:33:40,268 --> 00:33:43,688
And, there's been a big mistake.

447
00:33:43,772 --> 00:33:45,648
Am I to understand
you're actually declining

448
00:33:45,732 --> 00:33:48,025
the honor of becoming
a Starfighter?

449
00:33:48,110 --> 00:33:49,402
You got it.

450
00:33:49,486 --> 00:33:50,861
Extraordinary!

451
00:33:51,863 --> 00:33:55,616
For eons,
all creatures have dreamt
of being Starfighters.

452
00:33:56,159 --> 00:33:58,119
- Where you from?
- Earth.

453
00:33:58,203 --> 00:34:01,372
And we're not at
war with anybody,
except each other.

454
00:34:01,456 --> 00:34:05,167
Earth? Earth isn't
a formal member of
the Star League,

455
00:34:05,252 --> 00:34:07,545
and isn't due to be
approached until it matures.

456
00:34:07,629 --> 00:34:10,464
This is all highly irregular.

457
00:34:10,549 --> 00:34:12,883
Tell me.
Who recruited you?

458
00:34:12,968 --> 00:34:14,176
Centauri.

459
00:34:14,928 --> 00:34:15,970
There he is.
That's him!

460
00:34:16,054 --> 00:34:18,472
Centauri.
I might have known.

461
00:34:19,891 --> 00:34:22,143
(SINGING QUIETLY)

462
00:34:23,145 --> 00:34:26,856
Up to your old Excalibur
tricks again, eh, Centauri?

463
00:34:27,607 --> 00:34:29,483
Did it ever occur to you
that it is against the law

464
00:34:29,568 --> 00:34:32,194
to recruit from worlds
outside the Star League?

465
00:34:32,279 --> 00:34:34,363
Earth's in danger,
too, isn't it?

466
00:34:34,489 --> 00:34:36,574
And, no, I did not
use the Excalibur test.

467
00:34:36,658 --> 00:34:38,284
It was called a video game.

468
00:34:38,368 --> 00:34:39,910
What's all the brouhaha?

469
00:34:39,995 --> 00:34:42,788
After all,
he does have the gift!

470
00:34:42,873 --> 00:34:45,249
This may come as
a bit of a shock to you,

471
00:34:45,333 --> 00:34:47,668
but he doesn't want
to be a Starfighter.

472
00:34:48,420 --> 00:34:51,547
Doesn't want to be a. . .
Are you a coward?

473
00:34:51,631 --> 00:34:52,590
Are you crazy?

474
00:34:52,674 --> 00:34:54,300
You didn't tell me
about any of this!

475
00:34:55,010 --> 00:34:56,969
Return the money, Centauri!

476
00:34:57,053 --> 00:35:00,306
Return the money?
Are you delirious?

477
00:35:00,390 --> 00:35:02,391
Do you know how long
it took to invent the games,

478
00:35:02,476 --> 00:35:03,601
to merchandise them,

479
00:35:03,685 --> 00:35:06,479
to get them into
the stores by Christmas?

480
00:35:07,022 --> 00:35:08,981
It must be terribly
embarrassing for you,

481
00:35:09,065 --> 00:35:10,983
and I do sympathize.
However. . .

482
00:35:11,067 --> 00:35:12,568
But I saw him fight!

483
00:35:12,652 --> 00:35:14,403
He could be the greatest
Starfighter ever!

484
00:35:14,488 --> 00:35:16,238
That was a game, Centauri.

485
00:35:16,323 --> 00:35:17,364
A game?

486
00:35:17,449 --> 00:35:18,449
(SCOFFS)

487
00:35:18,533 --> 00:35:21,577
You may have thought it was a
game, but it was also a test.

488
00:35:21,661 --> 00:35:23,329
Aha! A test!

489
00:35:23,413 --> 00:35:27,917
Sent out across the universe
to find those with the gift
to be Starfighters.

490
00:35:28,001 --> 00:35:30,920
And here you are, my boy.
Here you are!

491
00:35:31,004 --> 00:35:32,671
Right! Here I am,
about to be killed!

492
00:35:32,756 --> 00:35:33,798
Killed.

493
00:35:33,882 --> 00:35:35,257
(LAUGHING)

494
00:35:35,550 --> 00:35:38,844
You don't seriously think
it's dangerous, do you?

495
00:35:38,929 --> 00:35:41,388
Don't be silly! Trust me!

496
00:35:59,616 --> 00:36:02,576
Xur!

497
00:36:03,870 --> 00:36:05,079
Xur?

498
00:36:06,665 --> 00:36:11,752
Yes, Father, your mighty Frontier
grows weaker by the moment.

499
00:36:12,838 --> 00:36:15,756
Do not call me father!

500
00:36:16,508 --> 00:36:18,884
You are no longer my son!

501
00:36:18,969 --> 00:36:22,263
You're an outcast!
Why have you returned?

502
00:36:22,722 --> 00:36:25,641
I have returned for
the good of all Rylans.

503
00:36:25,725 --> 00:36:29,103
With an armada of
Ko-Dan warships behind you?

504
00:36:29,187 --> 00:36:32,731
There are some Rylans
who would welcome me, Father.

505
00:36:32,816 --> 00:36:36,652
Star League justice
put down your Xurian cult.

506
00:36:36,736 --> 00:36:39,071
Your followers are
few and scattered.

507
00:36:39,155 --> 00:36:41,282
Star League?

508
00:36:41,366 --> 00:36:44,869
A refuge for weak worlds
not worthy to be our equals!

509
00:36:44,953 --> 00:36:47,371
That is for the Rylans to decide,

510
00:36:47,455 --> 00:36:51,458
and not for a dangerous and
evil child such as yourself.

511
00:36:53,128 --> 00:36:57,923
And yet, it is this child
who caught your master spy.

512
00:37:07,893 --> 00:37:09,768
(SCREAMING)

513
00:37:27,495 --> 00:37:29,163
Hear me, Rylans!

514
00:37:30,999 --> 00:37:36,295
When the green moon
of Galan is eclipsed,
Ko-Dan Armada will invade,

515
00:37:38,006 --> 00:37:42,635
not even your mighty Starfighters
will be able to save you.

516
00:37:42,719 --> 00:37:46,180
We shall see, Xur.
We shall see!

517
00:37:47,349 --> 00:37:50,684
(LAUGHING EVILLY)

518
00:37:59,110 --> 00:38:00,694
You still want to go?

519
00:38:00,779 --> 00:38:02,363
And miss all the excitement?

520
00:38:08,286 --> 00:38:09,411
Little brat.

521
00:38:09,496 --> 00:38:11,789
I invent the game,
find the kid,
drag him up there,

522
00:38:11,873 --> 00:38:14,291
and he doesn't want
to be a Starfighter.

523
00:38:14,376 --> 00:38:15,834
I give up!

524
00:38:52,288 --> 00:38:56,417
ROBOT: Control, do you copy
our star angle difference
from parking angle?

525
00:38:57,585 --> 00:39:02,172
Delta beta two at six,
delta gamma three at five.

526
00:39:07,762 --> 00:39:10,764
Emperor Xur ordered me
to bring his scepter.

527
00:39:12,767 --> 00:39:14,393
Let him enter.

528
00:39:14,477 --> 00:39:16,937
ROBOT: Target vector
remains on scope.

529
00:39:31,619 --> 00:39:35,080
Just like your Ko-Dan emperor's,
isn't it, Commander Kril?

530
00:39:35,165 --> 00:39:41,420
It takes more than
a scepter to rule,
Xur, even on Rylos.

531
00:39:44,132 --> 00:39:45,841
You're right, Kril.

532
00:39:47,677 --> 00:39:50,179
It does take more than a scepter.

533
00:39:55,727 --> 00:39:57,853
(LAUGHING)

534
00:39:58,980 --> 00:40:01,440
How long must we endure this fool?

535
00:40:03,401 --> 00:40:05,235
We have a break in the Frontier.

536
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:07,112
Fire the meteor gun!

537
00:40:08,698 --> 00:40:12,868
My dear Ko-Dan friends!
Lest we forget,

538
00:40:12,952 --> 00:40:16,789
it was your emperor who granted
me command of this Armada.

539
00:40:16,873 --> 00:40:19,792
For only I hold
the secret to the Frontier.

540
00:40:20,543 --> 00:40:23,212
Only I know the location
of the Starfighter base.

541
00:40:23,296 --> 00:40:27,007
And therefore,
only I will give
the order to fire!

542
00:40:31,304 --> 00:40:33,138
Forgive me, Xur.

543
00:40:39,604 --> 00:40:42,022
You are forgiven,
Commander Kril.

544
00:40:45,610 --> 00:40:49,071
Meteor gunner. . .fire.

545
00:41:08,967 --> 00:41:11,051
(ALL CHATTERING)

546
00:41:22,105 --> 00:41:23,397
Sergeant!

547
00:41:25,859 --> 00:41:29,570
I have an unidentified
incoming object in
Sector 31, sir.

548
00:41:33,783 --> 00:41:36,451
They're headed for
the base! Alert!

549
00:41:36,536 --> 00:41:37,703
We are under attack!

550
00:41:37,787 --> 00:41:40,164
(ON PA) I repeat,
we are under attack!

551
00:41:41,249 --> 00:41:43,709
Activate automatic repulser guns.

552
00:42:04,189 --> 00:42:05,772
(BEEPING)

553
00:42:26,794 --> 00:42:27,961
(FIRES)

554
00:42:37,805 --> 00:42:40,933
WOMAN ON PA:
Condition Red! Condition Red!

555
00:42:49,984 --> 00:42:51,860
At last, it is done!

556
00:42:53,446 --> 00:42:55,656
Soon the Frontier will be down

557
00:42:55,823 --> 00:42:58,075
and they will bow
to their new emperor!

558
00:42:59,077 --> 00:43:00,702
Or I will darken
the sky with their ashes.

559
00:43:00,787 --> 00:43:02,663
Commander,
the Xurian spy reports

560
00:43:02,747 --> 00:43:04,665
that one Starfighter has escaped.

561
00:43:05,583 --> 00:43:06,959
Escaped?

562
00:43:12,257 --> 00:43:14,132
(TOOLS CLANKING)

563
00:43:19,889 --> 00:43:21,098
You sure I can't give you a hand?

564
00:43:21,182 --> 00:43:23,267
You've done quite enough
already. Thank you.

565
00:43:23,351 --> 00:43:24,518
Well. . .

566
00:43:26,312 --> 00:43:28,230
It's only a few more
miles from here. I guess. . .

567
00:43:28,314 --> 00:43:30,274
I guess I can walk it.

568
00:43:30,358 --> 00:43:33,568
So long!
Bye, Centauri!

569
00:43:45,790 --> 00:43:47,541
Oh, Alex!

570
00:43:49,544 --> 00:43:50,627
Here!

571
00:43:55,091 --> 00:43:57,134
Hey, listen. I can't take
a present from you, Centauri.

572
00:43:57,218 --> 00:43:58,343
(SCOFFS)

573
00:43:58,428 --> 00:43:59,720
He reduces me to poverty again

574
00:43:59,804 --> 00:44:01,388
and he thinks I'm
giving him a present.

575
00:44:01,472 --> 00:44:02,723
What a world this is.

576
00:44:02,849 --> 00:44:04,099
What is it, then?

577
00:44:04,183 --> 00:44:06,101
It's a second chance, my boy!

578
00:44:06,185 --> 00:44:09,563
If you change your mind,
just tap the communo-crystals.

579
00:44:14,110 --> 00:44:16,570
Keep it.
Alex, Alex!

580
00:44:16,654 --> 00:44:19,573
You're walking away
from history. History!

581
00:44:19,657 --> 00:44:23,160
Did Chris Columbus say
he wanted to stay home? No!

582
00:44:23,244 --> 00:44:25,829
What if the Wright Brothers
thought that only birds should fly?

583
00:44:25,913 --> 00:44:29,708
And did Geloca think the Yulus
were too ugly to save?

584
00:44:29,792 --> 00:44:31,251
Who's Geloca?

585
00:44:33,129 --> 00:44:34,504
Never mind.

586
00:44:36,132 --> 00:44:37,424
Listen, Centauri.
I'm not any of those guys.

587
00:44:37,508 --> 00:44:39,009
I'm a kid from a trailer park.

588
00:44:39,093 --> 00:44:42,721
If that's what you think,
then that's all you'll ever be!

589
00:44:46,684 --> 00:44:47,893
(ENGINE FIRES)

590
00:45:13,461 --> 00:45:14,878
Hey, Maggie!

591
00:45:16,672 --> 00:45:18,632
Listen to this. You're not
going to believe this.

592
00:45:19,509 --> 00:45:20,592
I told you, Alex.

593
00:45:20,676 --> 00:45:21,718
Me and my. . .
How did you put it?

594
00:45:21,803 --> 00:45:25,263
"Strange sexual urges,"
aren't talking to you anymore.

595
00:45:36,484 --> 00:45:37,859
(SNORING)

596
00:45:56,921 --> 00:45:58,422
(LOUD SNORING)

597
00:46:06,097 --> 00:46:07,139
Who's there!

598
00:46:07,223 --> 00:46:09,516
Shh! You're gonna
wake up Louis.

599
00:46:18,359 --> 00:46:20,193
Hey, you look like me!

600
00:46:20,361 --> 00:46:22,195
Of course I do.
I'm the beta unit.

601
00:46:23,197 --> 00:46:25,407
What the hell's a beta unit?

602
00:46:25,700 --> 00:46:31,788
A beta unit is a simuloid,
an exact duplicate of you,
only not as loud.

603
00:46:33,249 --> 00:46:34,291
Huh?

604
00:46:34,375 --> 00:46:35,625
I was in the starcar,
remember?

605
00:46:35,710 --> 00:46:36,960
We shook hands?

606
00:46:37,044 --> 00:46:39,463
I became you, unfortunately.

607
00:46:41,257 --> 00:46:43,550
Let me get this straight.
You're a robot?

608
00:46:43,801 --> 00:46:45,844
I beg your pardon.

609
00:46:46,554 --> 00:46:50,265
I'm a state-of-the-art,
top-of-the-line beta unit,

610
00:46:50,349 --> 00:46:53,977
put here as a courtesy replacement
for while you're away.

611
00:46:54,061 --> 00:46:55,854
Lucky me.

612
00:46:55,938 --> 00:46:57,814
Wait a minute.
What are you doing back?

613
00:46:57,899 --> 00:46:59,566
Are you kidding?
It's war up there!

614
00:46:59,650 --> 00:47:02,736
Oh. Save the whales
and not the universe, huh?

615
00:47:03,446 --> 00:47:05,322
Well, why don't you
go up there and fight?

616
00:47:05,406 --> 00:47:07,908
Simuloids can't fight.
We're not allowed.

617
00:47:07,992 --> 00:47:10,410
Well, tell them that
you're me! Pretend!

618
00:47:10,536 --> 00:47:12,954
Be quiet, Alex.

619
00:47:13,039 --> 00:47:14,706
BOTH: Sorry, Louis.

620
00:47:15,791 --> 00:47:17,083
MAN: Thanks for the lift!

621
00:47:17,168 --> 00:47:18,585
MAN 2: Sure thing, buddy.
See you around!

622
00:47:41,192 --> 00:47:43,026
MALE VOICE:
Greetings, Starfighter.

623
00:47:43,110 --> 00:47:45,487
You have been recruited
by the Star League

624
00:47:45,571 --> 00:47:47,864
to defend the Frontier
against Xur and...

625
00:47:49,283 --> 00:47:50,450
(GROANS)

626
00:47:55,540 --> 00:47:56,998
(GRUNTING)

627
00:48:02,547 --> 00:48:03,922
(RASPING)

628
00:48:08,678 --> 00:48:10,178
And, hey,
what did you do to Maggie?

629
00:48:10,263 --> 00:48:11,680
Do to her?

630
00:48:11,764 --> 00:48:13,181
We're sitting outside,
looking at the stars,

631
00:48:13,266 --> 00:48:15,308
and she sticks her
tongue in my ear.

632
00:48:16,018 --> 00:48:18,812
I screamed.
I'll apologize tomorrow, okay?

633
00:48:18,896 --> 00:48:20,313
You're not gonna be here.

634
00:48:20,398 --> 00:48:22,148
You're going back
with Centauri right now!

635
00:48:22,525 --> 00:48:23,567
What's up, Alex?

636
00:48:23,651 --> 00:48:26,736
Back to sleep, Louis, or I'm
telling Ma about your Playboys.

637
00:48:27,321 --> 00:48:28,989
(FEIGNS SNORING)

638
00:48:29,073 --> 00:48:30,323
You're blowing it, Alex!

639
00:48:35,496 --> 00:48:37,163
What the shit?

640
00:48:37,248 --> 00:48:40,500
I said, back to sleep,
Louis, or I'm telling Ma
about your Playboys!

641
00:48:42,587 --> 00:48:44,296
Come in, Centauri.

642
00:48:45,298 --> 00:48:46,256
Come on. Get back here.

643
00:48:46,340 --> 00:48:48,133
And take your Tonka toy with you.

644
00:48:49,010 --> 00:48:50,760
VIDEO GAME:
Greetings, Starfighter.

645
00:48:50,845 --> 00:48:54,097
You have been recruited
by the Star League to
defend the Frontier

646
00:48:54,181 --> 00:48:56,933
against Xur and
the Ko-Dan Armada.

647
00:48:57,852 --> 00:48:59,519
Greetings, Starfighter.

648
00:48:59,604 --> 00:49:00,979
You have been
recruited by the Star League

649
00:49:01,063 --> 00:49:03,481
to defend the Frontier
against Xur...

650
00:49:03,899 --> 00:49:06,026
(VOICE BECOMING GARBLED)

651
00:49:08,195 --> 00:49:10,780
Where are you?
Come on, where are you?

652
00:49:10,865 --> 00:49:12,198
Centauri?

653
00:49:13,159 --> 00:49:15,035
MAN: Greetings, Starfighter!

654
00:49:16,245 --> 00:49:17,537
Centauri?

655
00:49:29,550 --> 00:49:31,134
(ROARING)

656
00:49:34,263 --> 00:49:36,014
(YELLING)

657
00:50:19,684 --> 00:50:21,142
Oh, shit!

658
00:50:21,227 --> 00:50:22,977
Come on, Alex.
Don't be such a wimp!

659
00:50:23,062 --> 00:50:24,145
(ROARING)

660
00:50:32,613 --> 00:50:33,655
(EXCLAIMS)

661
00:50:40,788 --> 00:50:41,871
Centauri, look out!

662
00:50:41,956 --> 00:50:43,123
What the. . .

663
00:50:52,299 --> 00:50:53,633
(GRUNTS)

664
00:51:09,984 --> 00:51:11,067
Phew!

665
00:51:11,235 --> 00:51:14,028
Foul stench.
Dirty creatures.

666
00:51:14,280 --> 00:51:15,530
(COUGHING)

667
00:51:18,617 --> 00:51:20,243
Get a good look, Alex.

668
00:51:20,327 --> 00:51:23,455
You can bet your asteroids
you'll be seeing more of them.

669
00:51:23,539 --> 00:51:24,748
What?

670
00:51:24,832 --> 00:51:26,249
This is a Zando-Zan.

671
00:51:26,625 --> 00:51:29,627
An interstellar hitbeast,
compliments of Xur.

672
00:51:30,337 --> 00:51:32,756
Xur? Why is he after me?

673
00:51:32,840 --> 00:51:35,091
Somehow he found out
you're a Starfighter.

674
00:51:35,176 --> 00:51:38,762
BETA: So you see, Alex,
you got to go back.
You got no choice.

675
00:51:38,846 --> 00:51:40,764
'Cause if you stay down here,
you're dog food.

676
00:51:40,848 --> 00:51:42,474
Trust Centauri, my boy.

677
00:51:42,558 --> 00:51:46,770
Because in two hours, this place
will be crawling with 10 Zando-Zans

678
00:51:46,854 --> 00:51:50,774
with just one thought
on their microscopic little minds,

679
00:51:50,858 --> 00:51:52,442
kill Alex Rogan.

680
00:51:52,526 --> 00:51:54,068
Kill Alex Rogan.

681
00:51:54,153 --> 00:51:55,570
BETA: He's right, Alex.

682
00:51:55,654 --> 00:51:58,281
At least up there you'll have
a fighting chance in a Gunstar.

683
00:51:58,365 --> 00:51:59,449
Exactly.

684
00:51:59,533 --> 00:52:02,535
Meanwhile, down here,
they'll be going after Beta.

685
00:52:02,620 --> 00:52:04,120
- Beta.
- Beta?

686
00:52:04,205 --> 00:52:06,122
Of course. What do you
think he's here for?

687
00:52:06,207 --> 00:52:09,000
Wait a. . .
Wait a second here, Centauri.

688
00:52:09,084 --> 00:52:10,293
Alex, look out!

689
00:52:10,377 --> 00:52:11,628
(GROANING)

690
00:52:11,837 --> 00:52:14,214
(ROARING)

691
00:52:18,219 --> 00:52:19,636
Centauri!

692
00:52:20,930 --> 00:52:21,971
Beta, get a doctor!

693
00:52:22,056 --> 00:52:24,516
No. No native cures.
No witch doctors.

694
00:52:24,934 --> 00:52:27,227
I'm fine. Just a scratch.

695
00:52:30,231 --> 00:52:33,691
Now face it, Alex.
You're a born Starfighter.

696
00:52:36,278 --> 00:52:37,904
Are you with me?

697
00:52:47,581 --> 00:52:49,582
Okay, let's go, Centauri.

698
00:52:51,919 --> 00:52:53,461
Good luck, Alex.

699
00:52:56,507 --> 00:52:58,299
You, too, Alex.

700
00:53:03,389 --> 00:53:04,973
(COUGHING)

701
00:53:21,490 --> 00:53:26,244
Centauri to Starfighter Command.

702
00:53:26,328 --> 00:53:27,912
Come in, please.

703
00:53:44,680 --> 00:53:46,222
Hey, Centauri.

704
00:53:49,310 --> 00:53:51,060
MAN ON PA:
Attention all personnel.

705
00:53:51,145 --> 00:53:53,313
Starcar is approaching
Docking Bay 12.

706
00:53:54,732 --> 00:53:57,025
Centauri! Centauri!

707
00:54:02,156 --> 00:54:03,990
Hey, hit the brakes!

708
00:54:09,663 --> 00:54:11,581
- Grig! Hey, Grig!
- Alex!

709
00:54:11,665 --> 00:54:13,583
They got Centauri.
He's hurt!

710
00:54:13,667 --> 00:54:15,335
He's right over here.

711
00:54:27,056 --> 00:54:29,140
Ah, you see?

712
00:54:30,559 --> 00:54:32,060
Centauri brought him back!

713
00:54:32,144 --> 00:54:33,978
Yes, I see.
Don't talk.

714
00:54:34,855 --> 00:54:36,773
Does he have my money, Alex?

715
00:54:36,857 --> 00:54:39,525
I have a fortune
for you, Centauri.

716
00:54:39,818 --> 00:54:41,361
Now, please be still.

717
00:54:41,445 --> 00:54:42,695
(COUGHING)

718
00:54:42,863 --> 00:54:45,990
ALEX: It's here. It's all here.
Piles and piles of it.

719
00:54:47,076 --> 00:54:48,534
All for you.

720
00:54:49,370 --> 00:54:50,828
Ah. . .

721
00:54:51,914 --> 00:54:53,206
At last.

722
00:54:55,626 --> 00:55:01,172
Alex, I want you know,
it was for the greatest
good I brought you back.

723
00:55:03,759 --> 00:55:07,136
Of course, it. . .

724
00:55:07,805 --> 00:55:10,098
It never hurts to be rich.

725
00:55:20,067 --> 00:55:24,112
Until the next dimension,
old friend.

726
00:55:26,657 --> 00:55:28,366
I'm sorry, Alex.

727
00:55:29,076 --> 00:55:37,417
Centauri?

728
00:55:39,086 --> 00:55:41,963
The Frontier could
collapse at any moment.

729
00:55:42,756 --> 00:55:44,215
Alex!

730
00:55:52,850 --> 00:55:53,975
(EXCLAIMS)

731
00:55:59,314 --> 00:56:00,898
(FLUTTERING)

732
00:56:14,955 --> 00:56:17,874
(LOUD FLUTTERING)

733
00:56:28,052 --> 00:56:29,510
(ELECTRONIC SQUEAKING)

734
00:56:40,814 --> 00:56:44,484
BETA: Now I need an ear job.
Dying here. Dying.

735
00:56:54,161 --> 00:56:55,161
(GASPS)

736
00:56:59,416 --> 00:57:03,086
Alex, what the hell's going on?

737
00:57:03,170 --> 00:57:06,339
Louis, you're having
a terrible nightmare.

738
00:57:07,174 --> 00:57:08,299
Go back to sleep.

739
00:57:12,971 --> 00:57:14,347
Louis!

740
00:57:28,028 --> 00:57:29,529
Oh, no.

741
00:57:39,706 --> 00:57:43,167
Am I to understand there's a beta
unit taking your place back home?

742
00:57:43,252 --> 00:57:44,293
He's trying.

743
00:57:44,378 --> 00:57:47,463
So it's safe to assume that Xur
thinks you're still on Earth.

744
00:57:47,548 --> 00:57:49,298
Yeah.

745
00:57:49,383 --> 00:57:52,135
That could work
to our advantage,
theoretically.

746
00:57:59,143 --> 00:58:01,519
Ah! Now you look human!

747
00:58:04,064 --> 00:58:05,481
Is this my Gunstar?

748
00:58:05,566 --> 00:58:07,984
This is a prototype,
different from the other ships.

749
00:58:08,068 --> 00:58:09,861
She has a greater range,
more power,

750
00:58:09,945 --> 00:58:12,071
and a slight
weapons modification.

751
00:58:13,282 --> 00:58:14,991
And, of course,
she's got deflective plating,

752
00:58:15,075 --> 00:58:17,493
so she can withstand
several direct hits.

753
00:58:22,875 --> 00:58:25,042
From here, this is
where I navigate the ship,

754
00:58:25,127 --> 00:58:28,129
maintain life support
and propulsion systems.

755
00:58:29,548 --> 00:58:30,798
Okay. Where do I sit?

756
00:58:30,883 --> 00:58:33,426
Way up there,
in the gunnery chair.

757
00:58:36,638 --> 00:58:37,847
Hang on!

758
00:58:37,931 --> 00:58:38,973
Okay.

759
