we're gonna jump! Okay?

1013
01:17:14,338 --> 01:17:16,172
- What do you mean, "Jump" ?
- We're gonna ram him.

1014
01:17:16,257 --> 01:17:17,257
What?

1015
01:17:18,384 --> 01:17:20,969
Extermination Emissary
Zeta 6, one message.

1016
01:17:21,053 --> 01:17:22,971
Ready? Jump!

1017
01:17:23,055 --> 01:17:24,389
Alex!

1018
01:17:24,473 --> 01:17:25,682
(EXCLAIMS)

1019
01:17:26,058 --> 01:17:28,018
"The last Starfighter. . ."

1020
01:17:29,979 --> 01:17:31,896
You owe me one, Alex.

1021
01:17:38,237 --> 01:17:39,404
Alex!

1022
01:17:42,074 --> 01:17:44,326
Transmission pulsars
have stopped, Commander.

1023
01:17:44,410 --> 01:17:46,244
The last Starfighter. . .

1024
01:17:46,329 --> 01:17:47,996
Is dead!

1025
01:17:49,081 --> 01:17:51,416
The last Starfighter is dead!

1026
01:17:52,335 --> 01:17:55,003
Nothing can stop us now.
Ahead full.

1027
01:17:55,087 --> 01:17:57,005
To Rylos!

1028
01:18:17,109 --> 01:18:18,610
The command ship!

1029
01:18:23,449 --> 01:18:25,909
There!
The turret at the far end!

1030
01:18:27,661 --> 01:18:28,912
I see it.

1031
01:18:32,083 --> 01:18:33,458
Good luck, Starfighter.

1032
01:18:34,168 --> 01:18:36,461
Thanks, Grig.
For everything.

1033
01:18:50,101 --> 01:18:51,976
I love you, Alex Rogan.

1034
01:18:53,479 --> 01:18:54,729
Six.

1035
01:18:56,023 --> 01:18:57,148
Heads-up display. Check.

1036
01:18:57,233 --> 01:18:58,274
Five.

1037
01:18:58,359 --> 01:19:00,193
Lasers. Check.

1038
01:19:00,277 --> 01:19:02,904
Four.
Particle beam. Check.

1039
01:19:02,988 --> 01:19:04,656
Three.
Proton bolts. Check.

1040
01:19:04,740 --> 01:19:07,200
Two.
Chair control. Check.

1041
01:19:07,284 --> 01:19:08,827
One.

1042
01:19:09,662 --> 01:19:11,162
Let's do it.

1043
01:19:20,923 --> 01:19:22,006
(BEEPING)

1044
01:19:22,091 --> 01:19:23,675
ROBOT: Tracking alert.

1045
01:19:26,762 --> 01:19:29,305
Unidentified craft.
What is it?

1046
01:19:34,186 --> 01:19:35,603
Wait.

1047
01:19:35,729 --> 01:19:37,188
Gunstar!

1048
01:19:37,690 --> 01:19:41,901
So, the last Starfighter is dead?

1049
01:19:43,028 --> 01:19:46,489
This has gone far enough.
Seize him!

1050
01:19:47,283 --> 01:19:50,869
How dare you?
I am the Emperor of Rylos!

1051
01:19:50,953 --> 01:19:53,872
I and I alone
command this entire op. . .

1052
01:19:53,956 --> 01:19:56,499
Release me! I command you!

1053
01:19:56,584 --> 01:19:59,377
You will pay for this
with your lives!

1054
01:20:00,421 --> 01:20:02,755
All guns fire!

1055
01:20:11,932 --> 01:20:13,850
There it is, the turret!

1056
01:20:14,393 --> 01:20:15,852
Alex, now!

1057
01:20:17,980 --> 01:20:18,980
Yeah!

1058
01:20:19,064 --> 01:20:20,106
Got it!

1059
01:20:21,734 --> 01:20:22,859
Hurry, Alex! Fire!

1060
01:20:22,943 --> 01:20:24,444
The Armada's almost to Rylos!

1061
01:20:34,497 --> 01:20:36,039
(ALL GRUNTING)

1062
01:20:43,380 --> 01:20:44,631
(ROARING)

1063
01:20:44,715 --> 01:20:47,133
VOICE ON PA:
Escape pod activated.

1064
01:20:48,802 --> 01:20:50,637
Escape pod ignition.

1065
01:20:51,597 --> 01:20:53,431
The Gunstar is gone from our sensors.

1066
01:20:53,516 --> 01:20:55,308
Alert wing commanders.

1067
01:20:55,976 --> 01:20:58,228
Communication turret is destroyed.

1068
01:21:03,359 --> 01:21:06,903
All communication radar systems
are out, Wing Commander.

1069
01:21:07,446 --> 01:21:10,114
Proceed with a visual
attack formation.

1070
01:21:13,911 --> 01:21:17,830
Life support good.
Ammo packs at peak.

1071
01:21:17,915 --> 01:21:19,624
I think we've got
to use Death Blossom.

1072
01:21:19,708 --> 01:21:21,292
Remember,
Death Blossom delivers

1073
01:21:21,377 --> 01:21:23,628
only one massive volley
at close range.

1074
01:21:24,380 --> 01:21:25,797
Theoretically.

1075
01:21:25,881 --> 01:21:27,257
What do you mean,
"Theoretically" ?

1076
01:21:27,341 --> 01:21:29,425
After all, D. B.
has never been tested.

1077
01:21:29,510 --> 01:21:32,178
It might overload the systems.
Blow up the ship.

1078
01:21:32,263 --> 01:21:33,346
What are you worried about,
Grig?

1079
01:21:33,430 --> 01:21:35,139
Theoretically,
we should already be dead.

1080
01:21:35,224 --> 01:21:36,474
Mmm-hmm.

1081
01:21:37,351 --> 01:21:40,103
Open Death Blossom petals.
Switch is on.

1082
01:21:54,660 --> 01:21:57,287
Do not trigger D. B.
until we're within range.

1083
01:21:57,413 --> 01:22:00,039
Just use your lasers
until I give the signal.

1084
01:22:00,124 --> 01:22:01,165
Remember to lead. . .

1085
01:22:01,250 --> 01:22:02,667
I've been recruited
by the Star League

1086
01:22:02,751 --> 01:22:04,419
to defend the Frontier.

1087
01:22:04,503 --> 01:22:05,545
Now, are you ready?

1088
01:22:05,629 --> 01:22:08,256
This is it. Here we go.

1089
01:22:08,382 --> 01:22:10,091
Charge!

1090
01:22:23,522 --> 01:22:24,647
(SNICKERING)

1091
01:22:32,114 --> 01:22:33,364
(FIRING)

1092
01:22:39,538 --> 01:22:41,039
On your right!

1093
01:22:42,583 --> 01:22:44,042
Your left!

1094
01:22:45,210 --> 01:22:46,586
Evade!

1095
01:22:50,424 --> 01:22:52,884
Power packs are low!
We need time to recharge!

1096
01:22:55,179 --> 01:22:57,013
Laser power draining!

1097
01:23:05,522 --> 01:23:08,691
Grig, my weapons are gone!
Should I do it?

1098
01:23:08,776 --> 01:23:09,776
Easy, easy.

1099
01:23:09,860 --> 01:23:11,694
Wait till they're all
in Death Blossom range!

1100
01:23:14,823 --> 01:23:16,074
(EXPLOSIONS)

1101
01:23:21,413 --> 01:23:22,747
Fire!

1102
01:23:56,115 --> 01:23:58,199
We did it.

1103
01:23:58,325 --> 01:24:00,451
Yes, we actually did,
didn't we?

1104
01:24:00,828 --> 01:24:02,203
(RUMBLING)

1105
01:24:04,206 --> 01:24:05,915
ALEX: The command ship!

1106
01:24:06,291 --> 01:24:07,709
Commander, our guns are out.

1107
01:24:07,793 --> 01:24:09,419
Damage control is repairing them.

1108
01:24:09,503 --> 01:24:12,964
Forget the guns!
Ramming speed!

1109
01:24:21,807 --> 01:24:22,849
Grig, we need power!

1110
01:24:22,933 --> 01:24:24,767
Death Blossom's drained all power.

1111
01:24:24,977 --> 01:24:28,688
I'm working on it.
I'm trying to run boost.

1112
01:24:32,151 --> 01:24:34,986
All we have left is
life support power!

1113
01:24:41,660 --> 01:24:42,952
Grig!

1114
01:24:49,168 --> 01:24:50,501
All right!

1115
01:24:58,093 --> 01:25:01,846
Weapons on!
We have them now!
Fire. Fire!

1116
01:25:03,182 --> 01:25:04,599
(FIRING)

1117
01:25:17,321 --> 01:25:19,030
(GROANING)

1118
01:25:24,787 --> 01:25:25,912
Damage report!

1119
01:25:25,996 --> 01:25:27,079
(ALARM BLARING)

1120
01:25:27,164 --> 01:25:30,625
Guidance system out.
Auxiliary steering out.

1121
01:25:30,709 --> 01:25:34,462
Divert!

1122
01:25:34,546 --> 01:25:35,963
She won't answer the helm!

1123
01:25:36,048 --> 01:25:38,424
We're locked into the moon's
gravitational pull!

1124
01:25:38,509 --> 01:25:40,051
What do we do?

1125
01:25:43,889 --> 01:25:44,972
We die.

1126
01:25:45,057 --> 01:25:46,098
(EXPLOSION)

1127
01:25:55,317 --> 01:25:57,068
(ALEX WHOOPS)

1128
01:26:06,495 --> 01:26:09,956
On behalf of the Star League
and all citizens of Rylos,

1129
01:26:10,040 --> 01:26:13,209
I congratulate you on
your dazzling victory.

1130
01:26:13,293 --> 01:26:14,877
Thank you.
Thanks.

1131
01:26:14,962 --> 01:26:18,339
But as you know,
the Frontier is down,

1132
01:26:18,423 --> 01:26:20,842
Xur escaped,
and there is still danger.

1133
01:26:20,926 --> 01:26:24,053
So I was wondering if you
wouldn't be willing to stay on,

1134
01:26:24,137 --> 01:26:26,597
and rebuild the Starfighter Legion.

1135
01:26:26,682 --> 01:26:28,224
Wait a minute.

1136
01:26:29,017 --> 01:26:30,601
Rebuild the Legion?

1137
01:26:30,686 --> 01:26:32,061
Yes.

1138
01:26:32,396 --> 01:26:35,773
Of course, you'd have the help
of an old friend.

1139
01:26:36,942 --> 01:26:38,693
An old friend? Who?

1140
01:26:54,877 --> 01:26:57,712
Centauri!
I thought you were dead!

1141
01:26:57,796 --> 01:27:01,257
Me die and miss all
the excitement? Oh, no.

1142
01:27:01,341 --> 01:27:03,885
I was merely dormant
while my body repaired itself.

1143
01:27:03,969 --> 01:27:05,928
Now, I won't bore
you with details.

1144
01:27:06,013 --> 01:27:08,806
Suffice it to say,
you're on Rylos, my boy.

1145
01:27:08,891 --> 01:27:10,266
Stop thinking human.

1146
01:27:10,350 --> 01:27:11,893
That's lesson number one.

1147
01:27:11,977 --> 01:27:15,396
Now, lesson number two,
you've got a good thing going here.

1148
01:27:15,480 --> 01:27:17,982
Keep smiling.
Don't blow it.

1149
01:27:18,317 --> 01:27:21,944
Lesson number three,
always trust Centauri.

1150
01:27:22,112 --> 01:27:23,613
(ALL CHEERING)

1151
01:27:26,950 --> 01:27:28,826
CENTAURI: Alex, they love you!

1152
01:27:32,873 --> 01:27:35,917
You see, all Rylos
is behind you.

1153
01:27:37,294 --> 01:27:38,878
You've got to stay, Alex!

1154
01:27:38,962 --> 01:27:40,922
You will stay, won't you?

1155
01:27:41,006 --> 01:27:42,423
CENTAURI:
Of course, he'll stay.

1156
01:27:42,507 --> 01:27:43,674
(CHUCKLING)

1157
01:27:43,759 --> 01:27:45,885
That's very reassuring,
Centauri.

1158
01:27:45,969 --> 01:27:48,471
Grig, I leave it in
your capable hands.

1159
01:27:50,474 --> 01:27:51,933
I'll stay.

1160
01:28:04,613 --> 01:28:07,698
JANE: Alex! Alex!

1161
01:28:21,338 --> 01:28:22,755
MALE VOICE: Greetings...

1162
01:28:24,132 --> 01:28:25,800
Greetings, Starfighter.

1163
01:28:25,884 --> 01:28:27,259
Bunny, have you seen Alex?

1164
01:28:27,344 --> 01:28:28,636
Can't say that I have.

1165
01:28:28,720 --> 01:28:31,973
Well, ask Maggie.
She knows where he is.

1166
01:28:32,057 --> 01:28:33,975
She was with him.

1167
01:28:34,059 --> 01:28:35,434
Maggie, where's Alex?

1168
01:28:35,519 --> 01:28:38,104
Yeah, where's my truck?
Where's your boyfriend?

1169
01:28:38,188 --> 01:28:40,815
Mrs. Rogan, about Alex,
you see, he's. . .

1170
01:28:40,899 --> 01:28:42,400
(ALL EXCLAIM)

1171
01:28:44,069 --> 01:28:46,445
- What is it? What's going on?
- I don't know.

1172
01:28:56,248 --> 01:28:57,373
(GASPS)

1173
01:29:08,593 --> 01:29:10,177
Oh, my God!

1174
01:29:12,097 --> 01:29:13,097
(WHOOPING)

1175
01:29:13,181 --> 01:29:15,474
All right!
We're being invaded!

1176
01:29:42,961 --> 01:29:46,672
Maggie.

1177
01:30:25,170 --> 01:30:26,879
(MACHINERY HUMMING)

1178
01:30:49,903 --> 01:30:51,028
Alex?

1179
01:30:51,196 --> 01:30:52,363
Hi, Maggs.

1180
01:30:53,365 --> 01:30:54,532
Alex,

1181
01:30:56,618 --> 01:30:57,618
is it you?

1182
01:30:57,702 --> 01:31:00,663
I mean, is it really you?

1183
01:31:05,544 --> 01:31:06,627
Look!

1184
01:31:08,380 --> 01:31:09,630
My God.

1185
01:31:10,423 --> 01:31:11,715
It is you.

1186
01:31:12,300 --> 01:31:14,760
It's Alex! Alex!

1187
01:31:14,845 --> 01:31:16,387
Alex, what is going on here?

1188
01:31:16,471 --> 01:31:17,930
What is this thing?

1189
01:31:18,014 --> 01:31:19,557
(CLAMORING)

1190
01:31:26,439 --> 01:31:27,857
Is this your spaceship?

1191
01:31:27,941 --> 01:31:29,608
I don't know what's gotten into him.

1192
01:31:29,734 --> 01:31:31,443
I don't understand that.

1193
01:31:31,528 --> 01:31:32,987
It's so strange!

1194
01:31:33,071 --> 01:31:34,488
Wait. Hold it.
Hold it, everybody.

1195
01:31:34,573 --> 01:31:37,575
Alex, what is all this?

1196
01:31:40,078 --> 01:31:42,121
I've been to another planet, Ma.

1197
01:31:42,205 --> 01:31:43,289
Another planet?

1198
01:31:43,373 --> 01:31:44,373
(ALL MURMURING)

1199
01:31:44,457 --> 01:31:46,584
Who was it helpedfix my antenna?

1200
01:31:46,668 --> 01:31:47,668
Yeah, who stole my truck?

1201
01:31:47,752 --> 01:31:48,711
And cut my electric?

1202
01:31:48,795 --> 01:31:50,838
And ruined my stove?

1203
01:31:50,922 --> 01:31:53,174
Oh, that was. . .
That was a beta unit.

1204
01:31:53,258 --> 01:31:54,300
OTIS: Beta unit?

1205
01:31:54,384 --> 01:31:55,342
A robot.

1206
01:31:55,427 --> 01:31:56,760
Robot? What the. . .

1207
01:31:56,845 --> 01:31:58,053
Come on!

1208
01:31:58,138 --> 01:31:59,680
(GASPS) A monster!

1209
01:31:59,764 --> 01:32:01,390
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

1210
01:32:03,727 --> 01:32:05,186
(SCOFFS)
A monster!

1211
01:32:05,270 --> 01:32:07,229
He got them chains on him.

1212
01:32:07,355 --> 01:32:09,356
All right! It's an alien!

1213
01:32:09,441 --> 01:32:10,941
Oh, no, wait!
Hey, hey!

1214
01:32:11,026 --> 01:32:13,027
Granny, put away that shotgun.
What's wrong with you?

1215
01:32:13,111 --> 01:32:14,528
This is my friend Grig.

1216
01:32:14,613 --> 01:32:15,946
I want you all to
meet my friend here.

1217
01:32:16,031 --> 01:32:17,031
MAN: You got to be kidding!

1218
01:32:17,115 --> 01:32:19,491
Grig, this is Mrs. Boone.

1219
01:32:21,244 --> 01:32:23,370
Hello.

1220
01:32:23,455 --> 01:32:24,622
And this is Elvira.

1221
01:32:24,706 --> 01:32:25,748
Delighted.

1222
01:32:25,832 --> 01:32:27,208
Me, too. How you doing?

1223
01:32:27,292 --> 01:32:28,459
I do well.

1224
01:32:28,543 --> 01:32:29,835
And this is Granny.

1225
01:32:29,920 --> 01:32:33,088
How do you do?

1226
01:32:33,173 --> 01:32:34,632
And this here's Otis.

1227
01:32:34,716 --> 01:32:36,091
A pleasure.

1228
01:32:36,176 --> 01:32:38,385
Any friend of Alex. . .

1229
01:32:39,638 --> 01:32:41,472
And this is Maggie.

1230
01:32:42,641 --> 01:32:44,600
A very large pleasure.

1231
01:32:45,310 --> 01:32:46,477
Hi.

1232
01:32:46,561 --> 01:32:47,811
(CHUCKLING)

1233
01:32:50,857 --> 01:32:52,733
You must be Louis!

1234
01:32:53,026 --> 01:32:54,735
(CHUCKLING)

1235
01:32:55,487 --> 01:32:57,988
I hear good things about you.

1236
01:32:58,073 --> 01:33:00,324
Hear that, you slimes?
I'm famous.

1237
01:33:00,408 --> 01:33:01,992
(ALL LAUGHING)

1238
01:33:03,119 --> 01:33:05,496
And this is my mom.

1239
01:33:08,500 --> 01:33:11,293
You should be proud
of Alex, Mrs. Rogan.

1240
01:33:11,836 --> 01:33:13,087
You must all be proud of him.

1241
01:33:13,171 --> 01:33:16,966
He saved the Star League
and hundreds of worlds,
including Earth.

1242
01:33:17,050 --> 01:33:18,842
ELVIRA:
Oh, for heaven's sake!

1243
01:33:19,010 --> 01:33:20,844
Oh, my God!

1244
01:33:22,639 --> 01:33:24,682
Time to leave, Alex.

1245
01:33:24,766 --> 01:33:26,016
Alex?

1246
01:33:26,518 --> 01:33:27,685
I have to, Ma.

1247
01:33:27,769 --> 01:33:29,228
They need me up there.

1248
01:33:29,312 --> 01:33:32,064
Oh, Alex, I always knew
you'd leave someday,

1249
01:33:32,148 --> 01:33:33,941
but I never expected this.

1250
01:33:34,025 --> 01:33:36,235
Gee, can I go, too, Alex?
Can I?

1251
01:33:36,319 --> 01:33:38,946
Sorry, squirt.
There's only enough
room up there

1252
01:33:39,030 --> 01:33:41,699
for me, Grig,
and Maggie.

1253
01:33:43,368 --> 01:33:45,035
- Me?
- Yeah.

1254
01:33:46,579 --> 01:33:48,872
Alex, I don't think I can. . .

1255
01:33:48,957 --> 01:33:51,458
What? Come here.
Come here.

1256
01:33:52,252 --> 01:33:54,003
Why else do you
think I came back?

1257
01:33:54,087 --> 01:33:57,089
- Well. . .
- Didn't we say we'd be together?

1258
01:33:57,173 --> 01:34:00,718
Well, yeah, I mean,
together here or
in the city.

1259
01:34:01,219 --> 01:34:02,886
But. . . But up there, Alex. . .

1260
01:34:02,971 --> 01:34:04,430
Maggs, you got to come.
You see, I'm not. . .

1261
01:34:04,514 --> 01:34:06,390
I don't know when
I'm gonna be back.

1262
01:34:06,474 --> 01:34:07,474
(SIGHS)

1263
01:34:07,559 --> 01:34:09,393
Don't you see? This is it.
This is our big chance.

1264
01:34:09,477 --> 01:34:11,770
It's like what Otis says,

1265
01:34:11,855 --> 01:34:13,480
when it comes,
you got to grab on

1266
01:34:13,565 --> 01:34:15,274
with both hands
and hold tight.

1267
01:34:18,320 --> 01:34:20,571
Well, what about Granny, Alex?

1268
01:34:25,744 --> 01:34:28,495
You're right. I'm scared
of leaving here.

1269
01:34:29,748 --> 01:34:31,332
Why can't you just stay?

1270
01:34:31,416 --> 01:34:34,960
Maggie, I have to leave,
and I want you to come with me.

1271
01:34:38,923 --> 01:34:41,759
GRIG: Alex! Hurry!

1272
01:34:44,888 --> 01:34:46,555
